1 (c) Powers and duties. The Committee shall study and submit a written
2 report to the House Committee on Government Operations and Military
3 Affairs and the Senate Committee on Government Operations concerning
4 recommendations for creating an independent Office of New Americans,
5 including:
6 (1) a summary of the current demographic, economic, and public health
7 data regarding New Americans in the State and information regarding the
8 government services being utilized and underutilized by New Americans;
9 (2) a summary or survey of varying and successful approaches to
10 providing government services to New Americans in other states, with
11 particular focus on the topics of the role of education and training institutions,
12 professional licensing, housing, and support for employers and municipalities;
13 (3) in consultation with community-based organizations composed of or
14 serving New Americans, State agencies and departments that provided services
15 to New Americans, municipal government leaders, educational institutions,
16 and business leaders, information on:
17 (A) the existing State and local-level barriers for New Americans for
18 gainfully participating in the State’s workforce, economy, and business
19 communities;
20 (B) additional governmental services needed by New Americans but
21 not yet offered by the State; and
