1 (C) the transfer or consolidation of existing governmental services
2 for New Americans that would be more efficiently provided by a new Office of
3 New Americans;
4 (4) the structure of a to-be-created independent Office of New
5 Americans; and
6 (5) the proposed structure, duties, funding, and labor needs of an Office
7 of New Americans.
8 (d) The Committee shall be composed of the following three
9 subcommittees, with duties and leadership to be assigned by the Chair at the
10 first meeting of the Committee:
11 (1) Legal Services;
12 (2) Equity and Access to State Programs and Resources; and
13 (3) Workforce, Economic Opportunity, and Inclusion.
14 (e) Assistance. The Committee shall have the administrative, technical,
15 and legal assistance of the Agency of Human Services.
16 (f) Date of Report. On or before September 1, 2026, the Committee shall
17 submit the written report required by subsection (c) of this section.
18 (g) Meetings.
19 (1) The Chair shall call the first meeting of the Committee to occur on
20 or before September 1, 2025.
21 (2) A majority of the membership shall constitute a quorum.
